laboratory_examinations.findings: Appendix dilated, measuring up to 12 mm in diameter, fluid filled, and contains a thickened wall. Moderate periappendiceal fat stranding. No extraluminal gas or drainable fluid collection seen. No bowel obstruction is seen. Scattered colonic diverticula without definite evidence of acute diverticulitis. A small amount of free fluid seen within the pelvis, which may be reactive and/or physiologic. Trace fluid seen along the left adnexa.
